<HEADLINE> Armstrong to Come Back in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion Lance
Armstrong will return to competitive cycling in March after being
sidelined for a year for testicular cancer.
</P>
<P>
The American will resume training with US Postal Service in
southern California in January and compete in the Redlands Classic
from March 3-8 in California.
</P>
<P>
Following the diagnosis on October 9, last year, 1993 world
champion Armstrong received extensive chemotherapy and underwent
brain surgery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
