<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Krajicek Beats Becker in Stuttgart Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Richard Krajicek beat Boris Becker
in a clash of former Wimbledon champions in the second round of
the Eurocard Open tennis tournament in Stuttgart on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Krajicek overcame Germany's defending Stuttgart
champion 7-6 (12-10), 6-4 after the German had put up a tenacious
game.
</P>
<P>
Becker fought back from a break down in the second set to level
the score at 3-3 against the 16th-seeded rival. But Krajicek
broke again for a 4-3 lead and held on for the victory.
</P>
<P>
Krajicek has pulled even with Becker in their eight encounters.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Pat Rafter of Australia earlier reached the third
round after Swede Thomas Enqvist withdrew with a groin injury.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia beat Andrei Medvedev
of Ukraine 6-0, 2-6, 6-4, while No.9 Marcelo Rios of Chile downed
Karol Kucera of Slovakia 6-7 (7-9), 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten outlasted Morocco's Hicham
Arazi 6-3, 6-7 (1-7), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
No. 15 seed Czech player Petr Korda of Czech Republic also
moved up with a 6-3, 6-3 victory over American Chris Woodruff.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
