<HEADLINE> Nepalese Woman Gives Birth to Triplets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 22 (Xinhua) -- A 28-year-old woman living in
far-western Nepal gave birth to triplets within one day, the RSS
news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The woman first gave birth to a baby girl and then to two boys
in quick succession, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The childbirths took place before the woman could be taken to
hospital, but the mother and the three babies are doing fine, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
The woman already has a six-year-old boy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
