<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese PM Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Prime Minister
Rafik Hariri today paid a several-hour visit to Kuwait and held
talks with Kuwaiti leaders believed to have focused on bilateral
and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Prime Minister's Office said that
Kuwaiti Crown Prince and Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah
Al-Salem Al-Sabah held talks with Hariri on a number of issues of
common interest, but it did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
However, they are believed to have discussed bilateral
relations and the lastest situations in the Gulf and the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Hariri extended congratulations to Sheikh Saad on his full
recovery from a colon operation, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Saad, who spent seven months abroad to recuperate from
the operation and just returned home last week, said Hariri's
visit "embodies the strong bonds of fraternity between the two
countries and their peoples."
</P>
<P>
During his short visit, Hariri was also greeted by Kuwaiti Emir
Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Kuwait maintain a good relationship. Lebanon
offered political and military support to Kuwait in the 1991 Gulf
War which liberated Kuwait from Iraq's seven-month-long
occupation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
