<DOCNO> XIE19971023.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Urges Passage of Electric Industry Reform Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today urged the immediate passage of a bill by Congress which
calls for reforms in the electric power industry to ensure the
total electrification of the country.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said there is a need for the enactment of the bill to
meet the urgent need to restructure the electric power industry so
that it can help in sustaining the economic development of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Regulation of the electric power industry through the renaming
of the Energy Regulatory Board to Energy Regulatory Commission
with the key functions in the restructured industry is provided
for in the bill.
</P>
<P>
Other measures include restructuring and privatization of the
National Power Corporation and creation of the countrywide
Electrification Service Company which shall spearhead the total
electrification of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
