<DOCNO> XIE19971023.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trade Unions Participate in International Activities  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 22 (Xinhua) -- China's trade union
organizations have forged ties with counterparts in more than 140
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
According to information from an ongoing symposium on Chinese
and Africa trade union activities in the increasingly globalized
economy, some 150 foreign trade union delegations visit China each
year, with over 100 Chinese delegations travelling to more than 50
foreign countries and participating in related international
conferences.
</P>
<P>
The symposium, jointly sponsored by the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions (CFTU) and the Organization of African Trade Union
Unity (OATUU), opened in Beijing on October 17.
</P>
<P>
One CFTU official said that the international activities are an
integral part of trade union work, and that the Chinese trade
union organization has been more active in the international arena
since the deepening of China's reform and opening effort.
</P>
<P>
The CFTU is striving to develop friendly relations with
foreign counterparts on the basis of independence, equality,
mutual respect and non-interference in each other's internal
affairs, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have conducted exchanges and cooperation in areas
such as the realm of economy, technology, personnel, culture,
sports and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The CFTU views the symposium as a suitable channel to increase
understanding and solidarity amongst trade unions of countries
throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the CFTU has worked with trade unions and
non-governmental organizations in other countries and has hosted
more than 20 symposiums and lectures.
</P>
</TEXT>
