<HEADLINE> Greece to Conduct Large-Scale Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Greece will carry out a
large-scale military exercise from October 31 to November 6 in the
Evros region and the Aegean.
</P>
<P>
The annual exercise, codenamed "Parmenion '97," will take place
with the aim of training staff officers and military units in the
planning and execution of joint operations in a modern warfare
environment, the Greek National General Staff announced here
today.
</P>
<P>
Greece conducted two military exercises, codenamed "Philippos"
and "Toxotis," in September and early October respectively to
enhance the military's combat efficiency. 
</P>
