<HEADLINE> Tanzania Reiterates "One China" Stand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has always
maintained that there is only one China in the world, Tanzanian
Prime Minister F. Sumaye said today.
</P>
<P>
He added that China has resumed sovereignty over Hong Kong and
the Taiwan problem will be surely solved.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye made the remarks when he met Chinese ambassador to
Tanzania, Zhang Hongxi, in his office in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the friendship between Tanzania and China has a
long history and the relations between the two peoples are close.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng's visit to Tanzania earlier this year
has further strengthened the relations of friendship and
cooperation between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye said that in the new situation, economic cooperation
between the two countries has further widened and Tanzania has
confidence in Chinese friends.
</P>
<P>
While implementing a policy of openness and liberalization in
the economic field, Tanzania welcomes Chinese companies to come
to invest in agriculture, tourism, industry, mining and
infrastructure, he said.
</P>
<P>
This kind of cooperation benefits both countries, the
Tanzanian prime minister stressed.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, representatives of the two countries signed a
handover certificate for donation of the Chinese government to
the Tanzanian government to express the sympathy of the Chinese
government and people to the Tanzanian people for the food
shortage caused by serious drought Tanzania has experienced in
the past months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
