<HEADLINE> German Post Company Confirms Record Profits in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The German postal service Deutsche
Post AG today confirmed a press report that its profits hit a
record of 321 million marks (180 million U.S. dollars) in the
first half of this year, up 67 million marks (37.57 million
dollars) from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The company however said it expected its annual profits for
1997 would be about the same as in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Deutsche Post, now converted into a share corporation, will
seek a listing on the stock market next year.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the company registered a turnover of 26.7 billion
marks (14.97 billion dollars) and a pre-tax profits of 576 million
marks (323 million dollars). 
</P>
