<HEADLINE> Chinese, Ecuadorian Foreign Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen held talks today with visiting
Ecuadorian Foreign Minister Jose Ayala Lasso.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the Chinese government has paid close attention
to the growth of bilateral relations, and that the further
development of friendly cooperation is in the fundamental
interests of the people of both countries.
</P>
<P>
He said joint efforts will ensure mutually beneficial bilateral
cooperation in wide-ranging areas, including politics, economics
and trade.
</P>
<P>
Qian pointed to the smooth growth of bilateral ties over the
past 17 years, and noted that the two countries have witnessed
remarkable progress in economic and technological cooperation. He
also pointed to increased trade exchanges, and increased mutual
understanding and support on international issues.
</P>
<P>
Jose Ayala Lasso said the Ecuadorian government and people
appreciate China's achievements in reform and opening, and noted
that Ecuador values its friendship with China.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the goal of the current visit is to
enhance mutual understanding and promote friendly cooperative
relations.
</P>
<P>
Ayala said the Ecuadorian government is fully satisfied with
the expansion of bilateral relations, especially in terms of
economic and trade cooperation, and will continue to extend great
effort to promote the sound development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Ecuador's continued adherence to its "one China"
stance and full support to China's entry into the World Trade
Organization.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers concluded the meeting by signing a
protocol on political consultations between the two foreign
ministries. China and Ecuador also signed an exchange of notes
calling for China to provide medicine to Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Ayala also exchanged views on the international issues
of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Ayala arrived here on Wednesday for an official visit to
China. 
</P>
