<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Olympic champion Liu
Guoliang's poor form continued in the World Cup table tennis
tournament in Nemes as he lost the opening game to Greece's
Kalinikos Kreanga on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Liu, who swept the men's singles and doubles
gold medals in the Atlanta Olympics last year, failed to reach his
dizzying height in the Chinese National Games last week where his
singles run was ended by a less known player.
</P>
<P>
Kreanga, who jumped out of oblivion after a string of
impressive performances in the Manchester world championships in
May, clinched a lopsided 21-11, 20-22, 21-8 win over the
fast-attacking Liu.
</P>
