<HEADLINE> French Shipping Company Opens Route to Ningbo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- CMA, the largest maritime
shipping company in France, announced its November plans to open a
direct weekly shipping route between Ningbo, east China's Zhejiang
Province, and a number of European cities.
</P>
<P>
The company, the world's 14th largest maritime shipping company
which entered the Chinese market in April 1992, established a
representative office in Ningbo in January 1995, and introduced
trial shipping routes between Ningbo and Europe in late December
last year.
</P>
<P>
Company sources say that nine 4,000-teu container ships on the
new route will operate in a 63 day cycle and will anchor in Ningbo
every Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo is CMA's third largest Chinese port of call, following
Shanghai and Chiwan.
</P>
<P>
CMA currently carries over 7,000 standard containers to China
on a monthly basis.  
