Swazi teachers, who are on strike, have threatened to register
their dispute with the labor commissioner. The move aims to lead
to industrial action, if the government goes ahead with its
increments.
</P>
<P>
Teachers throughout Swaziland returned home empty-handed
yesterday, which was pay-day, after the government stopped their
salaries until they end their week-long strike. 
