<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rival Clans Sign Cease-fire Pact in C. Somali </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The elders of the rival
clans of Majerten and Habar Gidir in Mudug region have sealed a
cease-fire peace accord at Gaalkacyo in central Somalia, 600 km
north of the capital here.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the town said over 10,000 people, clan elders,
intellectuals and various social groups, have marched to and fro
the only tarmac road -- the green line -- in the town in
celebration of the peace pact signed by the two sides yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The central town of Gaalkacyo is one of the most sensitive
areas of the country where the most power ambitious clans of
Somalia live together. It has all the time been the center of all
conflicts between the Habar Gidirs of Hussein Mohamed Aidid and
the Majortens of Colonel Abdullahi Yussuf.
</P>
<P>
This has been the largest peace deal ever reached by the rival
clans of Habar Gidir and Majerten, observers here say.
</P>
<P>
The peace march was sponsored by two delegates from Mogadishu
and the northeastern town of Bossaso and people gathered at the
center of the town where the green line and clan-manned
checkpoints were dismantled.
</P>
<P>
Mr Hassan Abshir Farah who spoke on behalf of the joint
committee told the journalists that the contents of the agreement
included an immediate cease-fire, the separation of the opposing
militiamen and the relocation of all clan militia bases from the
town.
</P>
<P>
According to the committee, the eight-point pact also called
for the formation of a 21-member joint administration committee
that will run the security forces and jail of the town.
</P>
<P>
Mr Mohamed Hassan Shikhad, a member from the five-member
delegation that left Mogadishu for the peace deal, said they will
also send elders to the nearby villages and countryside to inform
the nomads that an agreement has been reached.
</P>
<P>
And whoever commits further killings or animal looting will be
caught by his clans men and handed over to those whom he grieved,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also contains an item that says the clans men of
the culprits will compensate for the loss and damage values he
inflicts.
</P>
<P>
This accord was prompted by earlier clan-based killings four
days ago in the town of Gaalkacyo where six people were killed
and others wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
