<HEADLINE> Helicopter Crash Kills Seven Near Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 23 (Xinhua) -- A military helicopter crashed
early today over the town of Torzhok in Tver region, northwest of
Moscow, killing seven people aboard.
</P>
<P>
The victims, said an Itar-Tass news agency report quoting a
search-and-rescue officer, included three members of the
helicopter crew and four passengers.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary probe suggests that the KA-27 helicopter was
conducting low-altitude night-flying when it experienced a system
failure at a height of 120 meters.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Federal Aviation Service, which carried out the probe,
said the KA-27 is a heavy multi-purpose craft which has been in
military service since 1973.
</P>
<P>
Helicopters of this type are made by the KAMOV firm, which is
part of the MAPO military-industry complex.
</P>
<P>
A formal investigation into the crash is under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
