<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Norwegian King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji, in a meeting with visiting Norwegian King Harald V and his
party here today, said that China is pleased with the developing
momentum of Sino-Norwegian economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China and Norway are friendly countries and bilateral
cooperation in politics, economics, technology and culture have
witnessed gratifying achievements since the two countries forged
diplomatic ties in 1954, said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Norway is a developed country with advanced technologies in
hydroelectric power, petroleum, navigation, chemical industry and
environment protection, whereas China is a developing country with
large market potential, Zhu noted, adding that the two economies
are complementary and their cooperation would have broad
prospects.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that King Harald V has always paid kind
attention to the growth of Sino-Norwegian friendly links. Many
entrepreneurs are accompanying the King on his China tour and they
will explore concrete ways of advancing bilateral cooperation with
their Chinese counterparts, Zhu remarked.
</P>
<P>
The sustained, fast and healthy growth of China's economy has
provided broad prospects for Sino-Norwegian economic cooperation,
Zhu said, noting that the present China visit by King Harald V
will help boost the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
King Harald V expressed his thanks for the enthusiastic welcome
he received from the Chinese people. He said China is undergoing
great changes, and that he desires to acquaint himself still more
with the country during the visit.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the king voiced his hope that Norway-China ties will
be further promoted.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also briefed the Norwegian king on China's economic
situation and development strategy. 
</P>
