<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's legislators today
continued to debate a motion tabled by a member of the Provisional
Legislative Council (PLC) to thank Chief Executive Tung Chee-Hwa
for his policy address which was made earlier this month at the
PLC.
</P>
<P>
The PLC members generally held that the policy address made by
Tung Chee-Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of China, on October 8 is
forward-looking and pragmatic.
</P>
<P>
Proposing the motion of thanks, PLC member Leung Che-hung said
on Wednesday that Tung's policy address entitled "Building Hong
Kong for a New Era" has outlined the future of Hong Kong from the
point of view of long-term development.
</P>
<P>
The address is of great significance for it is the first policy
address ever drawn up by the Hong Kong people themselves, Leung
said.
</P>
<P>
In his policy address, Tung said that after Hong Kong was
reunited with China on July 1, the Hong Kong people have begun to
write their own history and must work to build Hong Kong for
themselves and for future generations: a Hong Kong that is
civilized, prosperous, stable and democratic, filled with a new
vitality.
</P>
<P>
The debate will be adjourned after PLC members have expressed
their opinions and will be resumed on October 29 at a meeting to
be attended by public officials.  
</P>
