<HEADLINE> 6 More Die in Gedo, Somalia Under Rains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The rain victims continue to
rise in the south and southwestern regions of Somalia as Jubba
river has overflowed banks, flooding large tracts of land.
</P>
<P>
At least six more people are reported to have died in Gedo
region in the past two days where the heavy rains have washed
away thousands of hectares of farmland.
</P>
<P>
In the district of Sakow, 57 domestic animals, mainly cattle
and goats were killed while 31 underground food depots were
destroyed by the flood water of Jubba river.
</P>
<P>
Elders of the town said more than 6,000 tons of sorghum and
maize were swept away by the water, while over 200 families have
fled their houses in the region. 
