maintenance of direct contacts between leaders of different
countries will facilitate exchanges of opinion concerning the
future of the world and friendship between people. He said related
efforts will be conducive to increasing mutual understanding and
enhancing mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jiang cited the ancient Chinese proverb: "Distance does not
hinder mutual understanding, and people living thousands of miles
apart can still be neighbors." Jiang said that China and Norway,
which sit at opposite ends of the Eurasian Continent and have
different domestic conditions, nonetheless have no fundamental
conflicts of interests and share identical historical experiences.
</P>
<P>
