<HEADLINE> Int'l Household Appliances Show Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition on
household appliances was opened in Shanghai today. It is the first
such show held in China.
</P>
<P>
More than 130 manufacturers from 17 countries and regions like
the United States, Germany, Britain, Israel and Turkey attended
the four-day event.
</P>
<P>
A number of world's name-brand products, such as Haier, Philips
and Siemens, are on display at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
In the coming three years, China is expected to have a
fast-growing demand for household appliances.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the country sold 9.53 million refrigerators, 6.74
million air conditioners and more than 10 million washing machines.
</P>
<P>
The country has set a goal to make all counties nationwide have
the access to electricity-supply by the turn of the century, which
is expected to increase the country's demand for the appliances.
</P>
<P>
Up to 85 percent families in the country's large cities are
planning to upgrade their household appliances in the coming few
years, as a result of markedly enhancement of living
standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
