<HEADLINE> ADB Institute to Open in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
Institute, a development "think tank" and a high-level training
center, will be officially inaugurated in Tokyo on December 10
this year, the ADB said today.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, the Manila-based financial body said the
institute will carry out innovative development research and
provide development management training for top-level policy
makers and officials of public and private institutions from the
bank's developing members.
</P>
<P>
The institute will seek to deepen understanding of critical
issues affecting the Asia-Pacific, help countries identify
development strategies suited to their particular conditions, and
facilitate the practical applications of these strategies, the
bank said.
</P>
<P>
Former Philippine secretary of finance Jesus Estanislao was
appointed by the bank as the first dean of the institute.
</P>
</TEXT>
