<HEADLINE> EDS-details added Chinese President Meets Norwegian King, Queen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Among those who took part in the meeting and signing ceremony
were Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen,
Vice-Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC) Wang Hanbin, Vice-Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) Zhu Guangya, Chairman of the Chinese Government
Reception Committee and Vice-Minister of Water Resources Zhang
Chunyuan, Vice-Chairman of the Central Committee of the Chinese
Peasants' and Workers' Democratic Party Fang Rongxin,
Vice-Minister of the State Science and Technology Commission Zhu
Lilan, and Chinese Ambassador to Norway Zhu Yinglu, as well as
some other Chinese officials.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian Foreign Minister Knut Vollebaek, Chief Manager of the
Royal Family Lars Petter Forberg, and Norwegian Ambassador to
China Sverre Bergh Johansen were also present at the meeting and
the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Jiang presided over a welcome ceremony in
honor of Norwegian King Harald V and Queen, who arrived here
Wednesday evening at President Jiang's invitation.  
</P>
