<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Beaten in Stuttgart Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- World number one and top-seeded
Pete Sampras of the United States suffered a straight set defeat
6-4, 6-4 in the third round of Stuttgart Open tennis tournament
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the match against 16th-seeded Dutchman Richard Krajicek,
Sampras was broken in the ninth game of each set and lost the
match in just 59 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The defeat, only the tenth for Sampras this year against 46
wins, will not affect the world number one's place at next
month's eight-player ATP Tour World Championships in Hanover.
</P>
<P>
Of the top eight seeds, only U.S. Open titlist Patrick Rafter
remains in the field at the penultimate Mercedes Super 9 event
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Krajicek's win earned him a quarter-final encounter against
either Swede Magnus Larsson or Frenchman Fabrice Santoro.
</P>
</TEXT>
