<DOCNO> XIE19971023.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Stock Market Hits Four-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Philippine
Stock Exchange nosedived today amid rising concerns over an
open-ended regional currency crisis, with its main index Phisix
plunging 96.06 points or 4.98 percent to a four-year low of
1,832.91.
</P>
<P>
The 30-share Philippine Stock Exchange Index (Phisix) once fell
to as low as 1,809.82 points just more than two hours after
trading opened. But the index managed to regain some lost
territory in late trading.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts said the plunge in the local bourse was due to
the downtrend in markets elsewhere in Asia, particularly in Hong
Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Investors are now worrying that the current regional currency
and stock crisis is expanding and prolonging as it is now striking
Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
They predicted more "bloody" days ahead in the local bourse as
long as the current currency crisis persists, adding that it is
possible for the Phisix to fall to 1,600 to 1,650 points.
</P>
<P>
The Phisix, which has been declining since Monday, lost a total
of 217.97 points or 10.62 percent during the past four trading
sessions. On Wednesday, the barometer index dropped 64.92 points
to 1,912.97.
</P>
<P>
The All Shares Index, mirroring the market's general bearish
sentiments, today shed 27.82 points or 4.5 percent to 586.94.
</P>
<P>
All subindices ended on the downside, with the mining sector
incurring the biggest loss of 173.94 to end at 3,001.84. The
commercial and industrial sector registered the second biggest
drop of 149.42 points to 2,674.58.
</P>
<P>
Value turnover reached 1.68 billion pesos (48 million U.S.
dollars), with more than 2.3 billion shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers, 128 to 8, with 36 of the 172 traded
issues standstill.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
