<HEADLINE> Nikkei Hits New Low in Tokyo on Plunging H.K. Share Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in Tokyo fell
sharply today with the key Nikkei index renewing its low for the
year on plunging stock prices in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected stocks on the First Section
at the Tokyo Stock Exchange, which rose 477.52 points on
Wednesday, closed at a session low of 17,151.55, down 536.06
points, or 3.03 percent, from Wednesday's finish.
</P>
<P>
Broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, dropped 30.86 points, or 2.26
percent, to 1,335.88.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section came to an estimated 450 million
shares, up from Wednesday's 431.58 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's stocks plunged Thursday morning with the blue-chip
Hang Seng Index falling below the crucial 10,000 mark at one point
due to increasing fears of a major fall in its currency.
</P>
<P>
On the Foreign Exchange in Tokyo, the U.S. dollar rose to the
mid-121 yen level, ignited by anxieties over Asian equities
markets.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was quoted at 121.43-46 yen at 5 p.m. local time, up
from 120.73-77 yen at 9 a.m. in Tokyo and from 120.85-95 yen late
Wednesday in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
