<HEADLINE> England to Play Cameroon in Wembley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 23 (Xinhua) -- England will play a friendly
against Cameroon in a buildup to the World Cup finals at Wembley
on Nov. 15.
</P>
<P>
Both teams have qualified for the World Cup finals to be held
in France next year. Cameroon qualified after achieving a
undefeated record in its group which also included Angola, Togo
and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
England qualified after winning its World Cup group, forcing
Italy to a play-off against Russia.
</P>
<P>
England and Cameroon faced each other in the quarter-finals of
the 1990 World Cup in Italy. In that match, England beat Cameroon
thanks to two Gary Lineker penalties in the extra time. 
</P>
