<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Arrives in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo
arrived here today for a three-day visit designed to strengthen
economic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It is the first visit ever to Vietnam by a Chinese vice-premier
in charge of economic affairs since the two neighboring countries
fully normalized relations in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are expected to sign some cooperation agreements
during Wu's stay here.
</P>
<P>
Wu was due to meet Vietnam's Permanent Deputy Prime Minister
Nguyen Tan Dung later today on promoting Sino-Vietnamese
friendship and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Wu will also meet Vietnamese Communist Party leader Do Muoi,
newly-elected Vietnamese President Tram Duc Luong and Prime
Minister Phan Van Khai on Friday and Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is the second leg of Wu's tour across Asia, which has
already brought him to Bangladesh and will further bring him to
Laos, Myanmar and Thailand. 
</P>
