<HEADLINE> Ding Shisun Re-elected Chairman of China Democratic League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Renowned Chinese mathematician
Ding Shisun was re-elected today chairman of the Central Committee
of the China Democratic League, a non-Communist party in China.
</P>
<P>
Ding serves as the president of Beijing University between 1984
and 1989, and was elected as chairman of the Central Committee of
the League in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
The League currently has a total membership of 130,000, most of
whom are intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
At today's first session of the Eighth Central Committee of the
League, Fei Xiaotong, Qian Weichang, Tan Jiazhen and Su Buqing,
all senior leaders of the League, were elected as honorary
chairpersons. Another five people were elected deputy honorary
chairpersons.
</P>
<P>
Also at today's session, Luo Hanxian and another 12 people were
elected vice chairmen of the League.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the Eighth National Congress of the
China Democratic League closed here Wednesday with the election of
258 new members of the League's Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the closing meeting, Ding Shisun, chairman of the
congress's presidium, called on members of the League to rally
closely around the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China with Jiang Zemin at the core.  
</P>
</TEXT>
