<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Residents Calm to Interest Rates Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Residents in Beijing have
reacted calmly to central bank's interest rates cut, saying the
move is "something within expectation".
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China announced last night that it would
reduce the interest rates for both savings and loans by an average
1.1 and 1.5 percentage points effective today.
</P>
<P>
A woman clerk at a savings bank in Wangfujing in downtown
Beijing said customers are fewer than yesterday, but "it's quite
normal". She said they did not have the interest rates changed on
the screen until 8:30 this morning after the bank opened,"for fear
of any possible leak (of the news)".
</P>
<P>
However more people came to deposit their money over the past
couple of days, "perhaps they had sensed something," said the
woman clerk.
</P>
<P>
An old lady seemed rather upset by the interest rate cuts and
regretted she had not put her money into the bank earlier. She
said she was surprised by the news and for a moment had no idea
what to do with the money at hand.
</P>
<P>
"But it seems safer to keep the money at the bank," she said.
</P>
<P>
The interest rates cut did not trigger a stock buying spree as
they did in previous occasions.
</P>
<P>
At a security exchange run by an investment company under the
Agricultural Bank of China, about 50 people were looking at the
flashing screen quitely and there were no lines formed in front of
the counters.
</P>
<P>
"People are more concerned with the government policies on the
stock market than the adjustment of bank interest rates," said a
middle-aged man."I have put part of my money at the bank and
invested some in the stocks. Maybe someday I can earn a lot. Who
knows?"
</P>
<P>
People in banking business see the interest rates cut as part
of the effort the government takes to help state enterprises out
of difficulties, most of whom have been burdened by high-rate
loans.
</P>
<P>
They predict an increase in their loan business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
