<HEADLINE> Yemeni President Leaves for Visit to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah
Saleh left here this morning for Paris on a three-day visit to
France.
</P>
<P>
Before departure, Saleh told the press that he will meet
President Jacques Chirac and a number of senior French officials
and discuss with them ways of promoting bilateral ties and
developing cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two sides will also exchange views on the
latest developments in the Middle East, the peace process and
other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
The president said that during the visit he will meet with
French businessmen and invite them to invest in his country.
</P>
<P>
There have been successful French investments in Yemen,
particularly in the areas of oil, gas and communications, he
pointed out, adding that more French investments are expected.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation of, and thanks to French support for
Yemen's democratization and financial and administrative reform
programs. 
