<HEADLINE> ADB Gives Loans to Vietnam, Bhutan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved three concessional loans totaling 113 million US
dollars to Vietnam and Bhutan.
</P>
<P>
People's standards of living in Vietnam's poorest areas will be
raised through a grassroots project to improve rural
infrastructure for which the ADB approved a concessional 105
million dollar loan, the Manila-based bank said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, which involves 60 small projects, 1,500 km
of roads will be built, irrigation and drainage on 20,000 hectares
will be improved and 500 villages will have potable water in
poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
The ADB today also approved an aid package to help private
sector development in Bhutan. The package consists of two
concessional loans totaling 8 million dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
