<HEADLINE> Sino-Dutch Agriculture Project Launched In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Dutch center, built by
the Chinese and Netherlands governments to train Chinese with
Dutch technology and equipment in animal husbandry, opened in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, and the Netherlands
Minister of Agriculture J.J. Van Aartsen cut the ribbon at the
inauguration ceremony of the Animal Husbandry Training and
Demonstration Center.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands government will provide 16.4 million yuan worth
of technology, equipment, and breeding stock for the center.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have been co-operating in agriculture since
the 1980's. The ministers of agriculture of the two countries
signed an agreement on the establishment of two training and
demonstration centers in 1996. A second center for gardening will
be completed in Shanghai on October 27.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Agriculture Minister Liu Jiang attended the inauguration
ceremony, then discussed strengthening co-operation in agriculture
with the Netherlands, with Van Aartsen.
</P>
<P>
Van Aartson arrived in Beijing today, at Liu Jiang's guest.
</P>
</TEXT>
