<HEADLINE> First UN Gulf War Payments Made To Chinese Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The first Gulf War compensation
payments granted by the United Nations Compensation Committee have
been handed out to Chinese citizens.
</P>
<P>
Nine hundred Chinese who were forced to flee Kuwait and Iraq
during the Gulf crisis got 2,500 US dollars each in the UNCC
compensation payments.
</P>
<P>
The compensation amounts approved by the UNCC are 4,000 US
dollars per person.
</P>
<P>
These are the first UNCC compensation payments to people who
suffered losses during the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in August
1990. Citizens from 63 countries were paid out of the first
compensation allotment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
