<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Ecuadorian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met
with Ecuadorian Foreign Minister Jose Ayala Lasso here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Ayala, Li said the friendly relations
and cooperation between China and Ecuador have been on the
increase and scored satisfactory results since the two countries
forged diplomatic ties in 1980.
</P>
<P>
The two countries share views on major international issues and
can understanding and support each other, Li said.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to make joint efforts with Ecuador, on the basis
of the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence, to raise the
bilateral ties to a new level, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the Ecuadorian visitor on the recent 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
China's present economic situation.
</P>
<P>
Jose Ayala Lasso conveyed the regards of President Fabian
Ernesto Alarcon Rivera to President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li. He
also extended congratulations to China for the smooth resumption
of its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said his country attaches great importance
to the relations with China and is ready to work together with
China to further strengthen such relations.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Ecuadorian government will continue to support
China's entry to the World Trade Organization, Ayala said.
</P>
