<HEADLINE> Russia's Chief of Staff Visits NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The chief of staff of the
Russian army today paid his first visit to his country's Cold-War
arch rival, the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.
</P>
<P>
Colonel-General Anatoly Kvashnin, chief of the Russian
Federation Armed Forces General Staff, met Military Committee
Chairman General Klaus Naumann, NATO's highest military authority,
and NATO Secretary General Javier Solana.
</P>
<P>
Kvashnin was accompanied on his trip by the newly-appointed
Russia's military representative to NATO, General-Lieutenant
Viktor Mikhaylovich Zavarzin.
</P>
<P>
When asked what his first impression in NATO headquarters was,
the Russian chief of staff said that the weather and temperature
were good.
</P>
<P>
But when further asked what the political temperature was like,
Kvashnin did not respond. 
</P>
</TEXT>
