<HEADLINE> Bahrain Refutes EP Censure on Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Bahrain has strongly
denounced the European Parliament's (EP) criticism of the human
rights status in the Gulf country, the Bahraini news agency
monitored here reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that during a weekly meeting, Bahrain's Consultative
Council members refuted an EP statement issued on September 18 as
a blatant interference in Bahrain's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The EP statement accused Bahrain of imposing high pressure on
opposition groups, saying such measures violated human rights.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain's Foreign Minister Sheikh Mohammed bin Mubarak
al-Khalifa said the EP statement was based on false claims made by
a political opposition group that works to distort Bahrain's
reputation and achievements in the field of protecting human
rights.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed al-Muttawa, Bahrain's Cabinet Affairs minister, said
the EP had no rights to interfere in the internal affairs of other
countries.
</P>
<P>
The EP statement coincided with a similar one dealing with
human rights status in the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, the UAE blasted the statement which
attacked the Gulf country's failure of giving two murderers rights
to defense before executing them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
