<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Algeria to Discuss Attack Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- A South African-manufactured
Rooivalk attack helicopter is to undergo evaluation trials by the
Algerian defense force.
</P>
<P>
Local daily The Star today quoted defense sources as saying
one of the helicopters is to be airlifted to Algeria this week
aboard an Antonov transport aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The trials could result in sales as well as a new marketing
initiative in north Africa, following attempts being made to sell
the helicopter to Middle East countries, the defense officials
said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, evaluations of the helicopter were undertaken in the
United Arab Emirates and Oman, but no decision has been made on
sales.
</P>
<P>
Rooivalk has been regarded as one of the most revolutionary
helicopters on the world market. The attack helicopters are to go
into service with the South African airforce later this year. It
has already been demonstrated in the British army and the Dutch
army.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's defense industry has previously supplied
Algeria with unspecified military equipment. It has also done
business with countries such as Egypt and Morocco for several
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
