<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Financial Chief Determined to Defend HK Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Financial Secretary of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Donald Tsang
reiterated his determination here today to defend the Hong Kong
dollar, noting that the SAR's economy remains stable.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the local stock market which has plummeted for
several days running, Tsang stated: "I am not worried at all,
because it is a market. A market, of course, depends on the
sentiments."
</P>
<P>
The SAR has 80-odd billion U.S. dollars of foreign exchange
reserves, without any debt.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think it is a matter for people to panic about," he
said. "But I believe very strongly in defending our dollars." "Our
dollars reflect the fundamentals of Hong Kong and the fundamentals
are exceedingly robust."
</P>
<P>
He is of the view that Hong Kong's companies are still making
high profits and they are turning in good dividends for the
shareholders. "It is very sound investment generally," he pointed
out.  
</P>
</TEXT>
