<HEADLINE> Share Prices Plunge on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices plunged on the
Singapore market today as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index nose-dived by 102.78 points to 1628.9 before bouncing back
to close at 1649.87, losing 81.81 points from the day's opening
level.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 307.8 million units, worth
765.65 million Singapore dollars (about 481.54 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 335 to 55
while 215 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Land was the most
actively traded stock as it registered a turnover of 16.44 million
units. It was followed by the Hong Kong Land which had 16.34
million shares traded. PISAPac was next with 11.37 million shares
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Uniphoenix led the gainers of the day as it rose by 45 cents to
end at 6.75 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 increased by 30 cents
to finish at 39.3 Singapore dollars while Prima and TAC 200 gained
10 cents each to close at 3.98 Singapore dollars and 2.1 U.S.
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS Foreign was the biggest loser as it
declined by 2.5 dollars to finish at 13.5 Singapore dollars. Asean
Fund lost 2 dollars to end at 10 U.S. dollars and Bukit Sembawang
fell by 1.7 dollars to close at 15.3 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
