<HEADLINE> Two Japanese Teams Abandon Bid on Mt. Manaslu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Due to bad weather, two
Japanese teams have abandoned their attempts on the 8,163-meter
Mt. Manaslu, the seventh highest peak in the world, Nepali
Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation said today.
</P>
<P>
The Japan Manaslu Research Expedition had reached an altitude
of 7,700 meters before they retreated, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, an eight-member Japanese team scaled
Mt. Manaslu.
</P>
<P>
But an 11-member Austrian expedition abandoned its bid on the
mount on October 12 due to bad weather. 
</P>
