<HEADLINE> S. Africa Invests $150 M in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- South African investors
have pumped 150 million U.S. Dollars into new ventures in Uganda
during the past six years, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
But Ugandan officials said the investment, which generated
about 20,000 jobs, was below expectations.
</P>
<P>
"South Africans have not participated as we had expected,"
William Muhairwe, the acting executive director of the Ugandan
investment authority, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The South African investment in Uganda represents a small
fraction of the 800 new investments valued at four billion U.S.
Dollars received since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Most of the capital inflow to the East African country went to
the manufacturing sector although interest has also been shown in
farming. 
</P>
