<HEADLINE> International Seminar on Spiritual-Social </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 African countries
will take part in the international seminar on the post-war
spiritual and social rehabilitation billed for October 27-30 in
Maputo, Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The news were released by Gustodia Mandlate, the Maputo
regional consultant of the World Health Organization (WHO),
Mozambique News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The countries which will particpate in the seminar include
Mozambique, Angola, South Africa, Chad, Ethiopia, Eritrea,
Liberia, Namibia, the Central Africa Republic, Rwanda, Sierra
Leone, Uganda and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The seminar to be hosted by the WHO is aimed at exchanging
ideas and seeking ways to solve problems caused by a protracted
civil strife, Mandlate noted.
</P>
<P>
She said apart from setting up a regional technical
cooperation network, participants are expected to work out a plan
of action in order to lay down concerned policies and strategies
and to find out solutions for the spiritual and social problems
caused by war as well as other catastrophes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
