<HEADLINE> Three Mozambican Navy Ships Submerged in Maputo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Three ships belonging to the
Mozambican Navy were submerged around Sunday in Doca dock in
Maputo Port, local newspaper Noticias reported today.
</P>
<P>
Another ship was still floating and swaying on the sea waves,
with a possibility to submerge at any time, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The paper attributes the submerge to negligence and lack of
maintenance for a long time.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, the ships had been dumped in the port
since February this year, and no one has made any efforts in
salvaging them.
</P>
<P>
The submerged ships would affect the repair work on the dock
and the route to a nearby fishing harbor, the paper noted.
</P>
