<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Djibouti Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
stressed here today that China attaches great importance to
developing friendly and mutually-beneficial relations with African
countries.
</P>
<P>
Li made the statement in a meeting with Mouhanmed Moussa
Chehem, minister of foreign affairs and international cooperation
of the Republic of Djibouti, and his party here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that Chinese President Jiang Zemin paid a state visit
to Africa and Li himself also made his way to Africa this year.
</P>
<P>
The premier said: "We hope to see political stability, economic
development and improvement of the people's living standard in
African countries."
</P>
<P>
Li said he is satisfied with the smooth development of
China-Djibouti ties, saying that the two countries have had good
cooperation in political, economic and other areas.
</P>
<P>
Li said China and Djibouti are "trustworthy friends," and China
is willing to work with Djibouti to further enhance the existing
relations.
</P>
<P>
Chehem said Djibouti government values its relations with China
and adheres to the "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
He said his government is ready to make greater effort in
further promoting bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of China's
National People's Congress Standing Committee, also met with
Chehem.
</P>
<P>
Wang expressed satisfaction over the cooperative ties between
the NPC and the parliament of Djibouti. He said he believes
China-Djibouti ties will be promoted through joint efforts of the
two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
