<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction Work on Huanghua Port Starts in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Construction work at
Huanghua Port, a major coal outlet for China, has begun in
Cangzhou in Hebei province, on the Bohai Bay.
</P>
<P>
The five billion yuan project includes four deep-water berths
with an annual handling capacity of 30 million tons. They will be
completed by the year 2004.
</P>
<P>
The port is the most costly in China since 1949. It is backed
by the Shenhua Group and Hebei Province. Shenhua is one of the
country's largest coal producers. 
</P>
