<HEADLINE> Ningbo Sees Rapid Growth in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo, a major port city in
east China's Zhejiang Province, has increased its import and
export volume 600 times over the past 10 years, according to local
sources.
</P>
<P>
The city has achieved 4.35 billion U.S. dollars in imports and
exports by the end of last year with its annual increase rate in
foreign trade reaching 50 percent at least.
</P>
<P>
Local government officials attribute this rapid increase to the
foreign trade rights granted to the city by the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation in 1988.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 50 export companies have been set up in the
city, while 114 local enterprises have been granted the right to
export their own products. Local goods have been exported to 146
foreign countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The city's export volume now makes up 26 percent of its gross
domestic product, according to the officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
