<DOCNO> XIE19971023.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Bo Wins Women's 5,000m With World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Bo, a new protege of
famous track coach Ma Junren, broke the world record in the
women's 5,000 meters to take the gold medal on the last day
competition of the Eighth National Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, winner of the 1,500m event, clocked 14 minutes and 28.09
seconds for the title, slicing 3.18 seconds off the previous mark
of 14:31.27, which was set by teammate Dong Yanmei in the heat on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Dong took the silver in 14:29.82, which also surpassed her own
world record. The third place went to Shandong's Liu Shixiang
with 14:38.14.
</P>
<P>
With eight entries of Liaoning province in the 15-member
finals, Wang Xiaoxia rushed ahead to lead the pack right after the
competition.
</P>
<P>
Then Ma's disciples exchanged leads in turns in the next few
laps before Jiang dashed ahead after 1,500 meters.
</P>
<P>
After six laps, only four were left in the leading group
including Jiang, Dong, teammate Yin Lili and Shandong's Liu
Shixiang, third finisher in the 1,500m.
</P>
<P>
Both Jiang and Dong broke away with two laps left to finish
one-two in the day's most exciting moment, and most importantly,
to break the newly-established world record.
</P>
<P>
Liu and Dong then jogged for a victory lap with a flag of
Liaoning team in front of the boisterous crowd in the
80,000-capacity Shanghai Barrel Complex.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very excited to win the gold and break the world record. I
dedicated the victory to coach Ma. I could never achieved such a
honor without him," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Champion Jiang revealed that coach Ma had set the tactic before
the finals, with some of his disciples leading at first and the
others to break the record.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xiaoxia, who paced the pack first, faded eventually for
the last spot while another teammate Wang Yanfang tailed in the
field, only ahead of Wang.
</P>
<P>
"Coach Ma told us to break the ryhthm of all the others," Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who went to Ma's training camp two years ago, said she
hoped to achieve good result in the 2,000 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"It's my dream to take part in the Olympic Games," she said. "I
will train harder after the National Games and I'm confident I can
improve a lot as long as I follow coach Ma."
</P>
<P>
Ma Junren, who expressed his confidence to break the world mark
right after the heat on Tuesday, said it's the right time for him
to make a comeback after two-years' slump.
</P>
<P>
"My athletes ran one and a half marathon daily during the
training and I asked them to take recovery nutrition 12 times a
day," he said.
</P>
<P>
The coach revealed that what the athletes feed themselves were
mostly old chicken soup and the Chinese traditional herbals.
</P>
<P>
Ma said the national titles were just the beginning of his new
team.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, I am not highly interested in home competitions. My
goal is to win world and Olympic titles," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
