<HEADLINE> Sharp Growth in China's Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- China's stock market saw sharp
growth in the first half of the year, attracting 200 billion yuan
(24 billion US dollar) from Chinese and overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors spent 13 billion US dollar on B and H
shares, accounting for half of the total collected funds in the
country's stock market.
</P>
<P>
The number of newly-listed companies has continued to increase
this year, with 149 large enterprises, mostly state-owned, being
listed on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges.
</P>
<P>
This helped state-owned enterprises in their move to establish
a modern enterprise system. One expert said that so many listings
in the first half of the year was rare.
</P>
<P>
Total trading on the two exchanges increased to nearly two
trillion yuan in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Trading in treasury bonds hit 1.86 trillion yuan on the
Shanghai Exchange, more than three times that of the same period
of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
