<HEADLINE> Chinese Party Official Meets Cape Verde PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a standing committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), meeting with Carlos Veiga, Cape
Verdean prime minister and chairman of the Movement for Democracy
(MFD), today, said that the CPC and Chinese government pay close
attention to Cape Verde relations and to its development.
</P>
<P>
China admires Cape Verdean efforts and achievements in
maintaining national independence and stability and in developing
the economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since the CPC and MFD established contacts in 1992, relations
have grown rapidly, Hu said, and the CPC will strengthen
co-operation with the MFD to consolidate long-term and stable
friendly co-operation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Veiga noted that the Cape Verdean government and the MFD are
satisfied with relations between the two countries and the two
parties, and that maintaining friendly party relations is the
foundation of relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that friendly co-operation between the two
countries, the two parties, and two peoples will grow further
because of his visit.
</P>
<P>
Hu discussed the results of the 15th National Party Congress
and of Party building.
</P>
<P>
