<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan, Britain to Conduct War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Jordan and Britain will conduct
joint military maneuvers as of November 24 to enhance the
kingdom's defense capability, semi-official paper Jordan Times
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The week-long combined arms training exercise intends to
"exchange expertise and knowledge and develop them until reaching
military professionalism," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The location for the exercise has not been disclosed yet.
Previous war games have been conducted near the desert town of
Qatrana, some 100 kilometers south of Amman.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that a regiment from each side will take part,
the paper reported.
</P>
<P>
A British Embassy official, speaking on condition of
anonymity, said that it is a "routine" annual exercise between
the two armies. The last one was held in September 1996.
</P>
<P>
Two joint war games have been conducted within the territory
of Jordan this year. Both of them were conducted by the armies of
Jordan and the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
