<HEADLINE> PLA High-Ranking Officer Meets Israeli Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Wang Ke, director of the
General Logistics Department of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA), met here today with a delegation from the Technical
and Logistics Department of the General Staff Headquarters of the
Israeli Defense Force.
</P>
<P>
Wang briefed the delegation on China's national defense policy
and army building.
</P>
<P>
He said the PLA, under the guidelines of the recent 15th
National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party, is actively
building the armed forces on the principle of "fewer but better
troops" with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Amiaz Sagis, chief of Israel's technical and logistics
department and head of the delegation, said he is pleased to have
the opportunity to visit China and witness the high-quality
logistics work of the Chinese armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived here on Oct. 21 at the invitation of the
PLA's General Logistics Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
