<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Steps up Efforts to Improve Ownership Structure (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- China is making new efforts to
readjust and improve the ownership structure in a bid to adapt the
productive forces to the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
"It is China's basic economic system for the primary stage of
socialism to keep public ownership in a dominant position and to
have diverse forms of ownership developed side by side," said
General Secretary Jiang Zemin at the recent 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
And this serves as the guiding principles for the country to
readjust and improve the ownership structure.
</P>
<P>
It is key to the economic restructuring to improve and develop
the basic economic system, while top priority should be given to
the economy of public ownership in the process, especially of the
state sector, economists said, noting that this reform is fatal to
the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 40 years, China had stepped over development
stages time and again due to radical ideas and policies, which
brought great damage to the productive forces and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
The CPC and central government began to introduce the multiform
economic development policy in the late 1970s, and dramatically
emancipated the productive forces with diverse forms of ownership
developing side by side as a consequence.
</P>
<P>
So, the non-public ownership economies began to have an
increasing proportions in the whole economic activities, while
that of the public ownership economy has been declining. However,
the latter's absolute output value has been growing by big
margins.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
