<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The suburb of Algiers was subjected to unprecedented
massacres of civilians last month, during which the army failed to
intervene. Today, the accusation of an army deserter and the
terrifying recount by a witness of the massacre in Bentalah, in
which 400 people were killed on September 22, reinforced the
suspicion on the exact role of the military in the killings.
</P>
<P>
-- France has wasted no time to help the victor of Congo
Republic, General Denis Sassou Nguesso. An Uzbek Ilyushin rented
by Paris landed on the airport of Brazzaville on Tuesday, from
which disembarked a campaign hospital, 15 French firemen and 25
French agents for intervention in rescuing civilians.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- Nearly 16 million Algerians are called today to vote for
their local representatives in a last step of a government bid to
revamp the electoral system. The process began in November 1995
with the presidential vote, followed by a constitutional
referendum in November 1996 and then legislative elections in
June. The voting takes place as the army launched a major attack
against the dens of the Armed Islamic Group (GIA), the most
militant Islamic group of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
