<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Finish Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing told
Ole Norrback, visiting Finnish Minister of European Affairs, that
China is confident in the development potential of Sino-Finnish
economic cooperation and trade.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Norrback, Li said that the economies of
the two countries are complementary, and there are many areas of
possible cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed hope that the two sides would strengthen their
cooperation on forestry, and that the governments would encourage
exchanges and ties between small and medium-size businesses.
</P>
<P>
At the request of his Finnish guests, Li also gave a briefing
on China's reform of state-owned large and medium-size
enterprises, and China's stand on entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Norrback said that his visit is an important measure to propel
bilateral trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Norrback told Li that during his stay in Beijing he had held
talks with Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Wu Yi on strengthening cooperation between small and
medium-sized businesses of the two countries, issues concerning
China's entry into WTO and Sino-European Union ties.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish minister said that it is important for both sides
to further economic and trade relations between the EU and China,
and China's presence in WTO would benefit all countries having
trade ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Norrback is here as the guest of Wu Yi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
