<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Runners Better 5,000m World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese women runners
reapt their world record-breaking feat in the women's 5,000 meters
at the Eighth National Games here on Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Bo of Liaoning province clocked unofficial time of
14:28.09 to take the title, while her teammate Dong Yanmei also
ran within the world mark for the second place.
</P>
<P>
The winning times of Jiang Bo and Dong Yanmei, two new proteges
of coach Ma Junren, surpassed the newly-set world mark of 14:31.27
set by Dong Yanmei in the heats on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The original world mark of 14:36.45 was set by Fernanda Ribeiro
of Portugal in Hechtel, Belgium on July 22, 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
