<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Jiang Bo Betters 5,000m Women's World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Bo and her teammate Dong
Yanmei reapt their world record-breaking feat in the women's 5,000
meters at the Eighth National Games here Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Bo of Liaoning province clocked 14:28.09 to take the
title and Dong Yanmei also ran within the world mark for the
second place in 14:29.82.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shixiang of Shandong province, finished third in 14:38.14.
</P>
<P>
The winning times of Jiang Bo and Dong Yanmei, two of the eight
new proteges of coach Ma Junren in the finals, surpassed the fresh
world mark of 14:31.27 newly set by Dong Yanmei in the heats on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The original world mark of 14:36.45 was set by Fernanda Ribeiro
of Portugal in Hechtel, Belgium on July 22, 1995.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, the 20-year-old Jiang Bo clocked three minutes
50.98 seconds to take the women's 1,500 meters title, only 0.52
seconds shy of the world record of 3:50.46 set by Qu Yunxia four
years ago in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Dong Yanmei, 17, made her first impact on Sunday when she timed
in 30:38.09 to threat the world record of 29:31.78 en route to her
victory in the women's 10,000 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
