<HEADLINE> Chinese Cui Wenhua Snatches World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese strongman Cui Wenhua
lifted a world mark to claim the men's 108-kilogram class
weightlifting title at the National Games here Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Asian record holder lifted 200.5 kgs in the snatch in his
third attempt, surpassing the listed world mark of 200 kgs set by
Taimazov Timur of Ukraine at the 1994 World Weightlifting
Championships in Istanbul. 
</P>
