<HEADLINE> Name-Brand Product Sales Drive in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The industrial and commercial
sectors of China's Shandong province held a month-long sales
promotion for a hundred name-brand products recently.
</P>
<P>
The provincial Economic and Trade Commission and Finance
Office, sponsors of the drive, say the products have a good
reputation for quality and after-sales service and have a large
market share. They represent the level of quality in the province
and include some brands known outside China, like Haier, Qingqi,
and Qingdao Beer.
</P>
<P>
The drive involved 32 large stores with yearly sales each
exceeding 100 million yuan. The provincial government says it will
bring the sales-to-output ratio up to 97 percent by the turn of
the century, and have sales in the province account for 40
percent, sales in other parts of the country, 30 percent, and
overseas, 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province is now a buyer's market. The local economic and
trade commission says that for 94 percent of the goods, output
exceeds demand. So, sales in large retail stores have slowed
down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
