<HEADLINE> Spirlea Finad for Bad Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Romania Irina Spirlea will be
fined 5,000 US dollars for remarks she made after her semifinal
loss to American Venus Williams at the U.S. Open, the WTA Tour
Player Review Committee announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spirlea, who was seeded 11th, lost the match 7-6 (7-5), 4-6,
7-6 (9-7) to the 17-year-old Williams. They bumped each other hard
during a changeover in the second set, which Williams described as
purely accidental.
</P>
<P>
World number seven Spirlea did not hide her displeasure with
the teenager in the interview room after the match. She said she
had been fed up with deferring to Williams on the changeovers.
