<HEADLINE> Road System Expanded in Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Jilin
Province is building roads to improve its transportation.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has invested 13.5 billion yuan in
road construction over the past few years, extending its roads for
32,930 kilometers, an annual increase of more than 1,000
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The expansion means that 94.8 percent of local villages are
connected with nearby counties and cities by road,
said a provincial report.
</P>
<P>
Last year, an expressway was completed linking Siping with
Changchun, the provincial capital. Three more expressways were
finished last September, bringing the total length of expressways in
the province to 313 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Many large-scale centers have also been set up to handle the
increased passenger traffic, and the province has expanded its
ports.  
