<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Hold Investment Forum Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh is set to hold a
three-day investment forum in Dhaka on November 5 in a bid to
attract more foreign investment for bolstering the country's
economic growth, said official sources today.
</P>
<P>
About fifty investors from Europe, North and South America and
Asia-Pacific region are expected to participate in the forum,
which is to be sponsored by the Board of Investment in
cooperation with the Economic Relations Division of the Ministry
of Finance, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Besides, over one hundred local investors, industrialists,
leaders of business community and financial experts are also
expected to attend the unique program designed to present an
in-depth assessment of both the challenges and opportunities of
Bangladesh, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the forum, the sources said, would be to project
the investment environment in Bangladesh, opportunities for
infrastructural investment, financial sector reform, international
investors' case studies and investment in the export processing
zones.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh would make strenuous efforts to attract foreign
investment in power, energy and utilities, transport and port
infrastructure, telecommunications, finance and banking and
textiles and manufacturing sectors, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government is keen to support financial sector
reforms and increase privatization together with a GDP growth
approaching six percent, and this means that there are excellent
opportunities for investment in the country, they added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
