<HEADLINE> Strongwoman Tested Positive at National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Xiaoli, who won a bronze
medal in the women's 83-kilogram category at the National Games,
was tested positive for banned drugs, a spokeswoman said here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zhang, who lifted a total of 282.5 kgs for the bronze, will be
stripped of her medal and be punished under the rules of the
International Weightlifting Federation, said the Chinese Olympic
Committee spokeswoman He Huixian.
</P>
<P>
But she failed to disclose the banned drugs that Zhang has
taken.
</P>
<P>
Two strongwomen were disqualified from the National Games last
week as they were caught of submitting prepared tubes of urine in
the doping tests. The Game's Competition Department then ruled
the two cases as positive against the two women lifters.
</P>
<P>
During the Games, a total of 480 urine samples were tested,
including those of all the gold medalists and record breakers, the
spokeswoman said. The other samples were from random tests.
</P>
<P>
More efforts for doping control were made in the swimming
competitons as "more than 500 samples were tested from the
swimmers," He Huixian said.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome the internaitonal doping control organizations to
test our athletes at any time as long as it is conducted in
accordance with the procedures of the International Olympic
Committee," the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
