<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Economic Ties Should Be Elevated: Zeng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Both the United States and
China must make common efforts to overcome difficulties and bring
to a higher level their economic ties based on reciprocity and
mutual benefit, visiting Chinese State Planning Commission Vice
Chairman Zeng Peiyan said here tonight.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to New York and U.S. business community leaders,
Zeng said despite encouraging achievements in Sino-U.S. trade and
economic cooperation, cooperation was not always smooth.
</P>
<P>
"An annual review of the Most Favored Nation status of China
has brought great difficulties to the enterprises of both
countries," Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
"The restriction on high-tech exports from the United States to
China exactly reduces the advantage of American companies.
</P>
<P>
"And the conservative attitude adopted by some American
financial institutions has resulted in the loss of large power
equipment contracts, which should have been won by American
companies."
</P>
<P>
Zeng said China's door was opened to all the countries around
the world.
</P>
<P>
Zeng, who is heading the Chinese Economic and Trade Delegation
on a purchase mission to the United States, said his delegation
will reach agreements with the U.S. side on purchasing commodities
including aircraft, crude oil and automobiles and on cooperation
in aerospace and energy industries.
</P>
<P>
"All these agreements reflect our sincerity to expand economic
and trade cooperation with the United States and the strong desire
of both sides to further strengthen the economic and trade ties,"
he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Zeng said China, the largest economy in the developing world,
and the United States, the largest economy in the developed world,
shared common responsibilities for addressing many significant
issues such as promoting world economic prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"With the coming of the 21st century, China and the United
States should further strengthen economic and trade cooperation,"
he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
