<HEADLINE> Chang Ousted at Stuttgart Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 22 (Xinhua) -- World number two Michael Chang of
United States was upset by Frenchman Cedric Pioline, failing to
enter the third round at the Stuttgart Open tennis tournament on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Pioline's 7-5, 1-6, 6-4 victory over Chang was his first in six
career meetings. It was also a sweet avenge of the fourth round
loss to the American at the U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed Goran Ivanisevic, number five Greg Rusedski, number
six Carlos Moya and number eight Sergi Bruguera, all joined
Chang's upset fate.
</P>
<P>
Croat Invanisevic's departure was forced by a sore shoulder
when he retired with Briton Tem Henman leading 6-3, 2-0.
</P>
<P>
Britian's Rusedski is one of the hottest players on the
circuit, but his superb form was stopped by a 5-7, 6-2, 6-4 loss
to German rising star Nicolas Kiefer.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Moya was dispatched 6-3 7-6 by Todd Martin of the
United States while his compatriot Brugeura was beaten 7-5 7-6 by
France's Fabrice Santoro, who won in Lyon last week. 
</P>
