<HEADLINE> Grenade Found near Sri Lankan President's Residence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan police
discovered a grenade in the vicinity of the official residence of
President Chandrika Kumaratunga Tuesday afternoon, police sources
disclosed today.
</P>
<P>
The grenade was found near a security post in the highly
guarded security zone around the president's residence. The army's
bomb disposal unit was called in to defuse the grenade.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the discovered grenade was of the same type
commonly used in the army. They suspected it was brought to the
vicinity of the presidential residence by the Tamil rebels.
</P>
<P>
So far no arrests were made in connection with the discovery.
Police investigations are still underway.
</P>
<P>
President Kumaratunga is attending the Commonwealth Heads of
Government Conference in Britain. 
