<HEADLINE> Mexico Issues Global Bond </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican government
issued a global bond in the stock market of Canada for 500 million
canadian dollars (360 million U.S. dollars), the Finance
Secretariat reported today.
</P>
<P>
The institution said at a press release that the new bond
will be put to auction by a group of important Canadian financial
companies, headed by Merril Lyinch and Scotia Capital Markets.
</P>
<P>
With the bond, Mexico becomes the first non-Canadian issuer to
put to an auction a global bond in Canadian currency.
</P>
<P>
The bond will have a term of six years and an annual
interest rate of seven percent in Canadian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Secretariat said part of the bond will be auctioned
in the United States, Latin American countries, Europe and Asia.
</P>
<P>
The source said revenues from this issue will be used to
refinance short-term governmental obligations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
