<HEADLINE> Industrial Output Rises 5 Percent in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ROME, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Industrial output in Italy, which
rose 0.5 percent in October, was five percent higher than a year
earlier, the employer' body, Confindustria, reported today.
</P>
<P>
The sales of industrial products increased 6.1 percent in
October compared to the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months of the year, the output rose 1.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The upward trend looked set to continue, with October orders 7.1
percent up over the same month last year. 
</P>
