<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Romania Ratify Cooperation Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and Romania today put
their good-neighborliness and cooperation treaty into force by
exchanging letters of ratification.
</P>
<P>
The treaty was signed on June 2 this year by the presidents of
the two countries, under which Ukraine and Romania will continue
to negotiate the division of the continental shelf around the
Zmeiny island in the Black Sea.
</P>
<P>
If the two countries fail to solve the issue within two years,
they will present their case to the international court for a
ruling.
</P>
<P>
After exchanging the letters of ratification, foreign minister
of the two countries noted that ratification of the treaty
represents a major improvement of their bilateral relations and
will lay a sound foundation for their cooperation in various
fields. 
</P>
