<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Import 500 Buses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka is planning to import
500 buses and 1,000 engine kits to strengthen its transport
services, sources in the Transport and Highways Ministry said
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the buses and engine kits, at a total cost of
over 15 million U.S. dollars, will arrive early next year.
