<HEADLINE> UNICEF, Italy Unveil Program For Albanian Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF) and Italy today unveiled a joint program aimed at
improving living conditions for Albanian children, the Italian
news agency ANSA reported.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF Director-General, Carol Bellamy, said the program
centering on prevention, will last two years and spend 3.5 billion
lira (about two million U.S. dollars) in enhancing the network of
social services for infants and young people in Balkan countries.
</P>
<P>
The Fund was established in 1946 by the General Assembly as the
UN International Children's Emergency Fund, to meet the emergency
needs of children in post-war Europe and China. Later, it became a
permanent arm for the benefit of children everywhere, particularly
those in developing countries. 
</P>
