<HEADLINE> Myanmar Drafts Laws for Patent, Intellectual Property </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is in the process of
drafting laws concerning patent right, intellectual property and
industrial design, said a senior Myanmar science and technology
official.
</P>
<P>
U Aung Koe, director general of the Scientific and
Technological Research Department under the Myanmar Ministry of
Science and Technology, disclosed at a seminar on intellectual
property here Wednesday that the World Intellectual Property
Organization (WIPO) is helping his country to set up a Myanmar
Intellectual Property Office, official paper The New Light of
Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
He said protection and enforcement of intellectual property
would induce more inflow of foreign investment and technology,
especially at the time when Myanmar has joined the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations.
</P>
<P>
"Myanmar believes that cooperation and consultation on
intellectual property are beneficial to the participating
countries irrespective of the level of economic development by
sharing the view that the commitment to protecting and promoting
intellectual property is a vehicle for economic growth and
cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, total foreign
investment in Myanmar reached 6.44 billion U.S. dollars at the end
of September this year, in which five ASEAN countries --
Singapore, Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia and the Philippines --
shared 3.148 billion dollars in 131 projects.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar, which began Wednesday, was sponsored by
the WIPO in cooperation with the Myanmar Ministry of Science and
Technology.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of Australia, Sweden and Myanmar as well as
officials of the WIPO participated in the seminar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
