<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Economy up 2 Percent in First Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- The economy of Ecuador registered
a 2 percent increase over the first half of the year, the Central
Bank reported today.
</P>
<P>
A study said that, if the effects caused by the El Nino
phenomenon do not affect agricultural output, growth by the
year-end might be 3.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Gross Domestic Product (GDP) rose just 0.6 percent during
the first quarter of the year, due to the political crisis, but it
jumped 1.8 percent by June's end after political turmoil receded.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank study said agriculture grew 2.5 percent in the
first quarter, but fell 1.8 percent in the second quarter due to
production for foreign markets, primarily of banana, coffee and
cacao.
</P>
<P>
The oil and mining sector swelled 1 percent in the first
quarter thanks to a growing activity in the mines. By the second
quarter, production of oil raised 0.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
