<HEADLINE> Civilians Injured as Sri Lankan Rebels Blast Bus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen civilians in a bus were
injured when a landmine exploded Wednesday in Batticaloa, Eastern
province, security sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The bus was traveling between Batticaloa and Kalmunai, also in
Eastern province, when a landmine was set off by the rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
Sources said the rebels could probably have thought that
members of the Special Task Force (STF) were traveling in the bus
as they sometimes use civilian transport.
</P>
<P>
However, there were no STF or security personnel in the bus.
</P>
<P>
The injured were sent to a local hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
At the time of the explosion, there were 60 civilians in the
bus. 
</P>
