<HEADLINE> 15 Cases of Cholera Detected in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen cases of cholera were
detected over the last few days in Ecuador's provinces of Guayas
and Manabi, due to the pollution of drinking water, health
authorities reported today.
</P>
<P>
In Guayas, the Health Director of the province, Victor Hugo
Mite, said the 12 cases of cholera were detected in Balzar, El
Empalme and Naranjito towns.
</P>
<P>
The official said they only act on the known cases but it is
likely there are many other cases that have not been detected so
far. He stressed the importance of giving information to people
about danger of the cholera.
</P>
<P>
In the Manabi province, three cases came about in the Cojimies
town, because of the pollution of drinking water caused by a
recent flood, which have triggered outbreaks of tropical illnesses.
</P>
<P>
On the other side, in the Esmeraldas province, about 10,000
inhabitants from 20 towns suffered shortages of water, medicines
and food. 
</P>
