<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, October 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian Yabloko faction would drop its
no-confidence motion against the government if it went through the
problem of the taxation code to the end, leader of the Yabloko
parliamentary faction Grigory Yavlinsky said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Yavlinsky told reporters that the document which his faction
considered to be "senseless and harmful" should be recalled.
</P>
<P>
He meanwhile voiced the strong doubt that Sergei Baburin
representing the People's Power bloc in parliament would collect
the necessary number of signatures to initiate a no-confidence
motion against the government. (Russia-Gov't-No Confidence)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. Defense Department issued an interim
policy Wednesday to request the military servicemen to turn in
their weapons to comply with a law prohibiting gun ownership by
people convicted of domestic abuse.
</P>
<P>
All the military's 1.4 million men and women are being required
to fill out a form to determine whether they had been convicted of
such an offense.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon expects the people affected would be in the
hundreds as most of the service members are young, unmarried and
unlikely to bring such a conviction with them, said Frank Rush,
the principal deputy assistant secretary for force management
policy. (US-Abuser-Weapons)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan Wednesday
presented his 2.583 billion U.S. dollars budget proposal to cover
the expenses of the United Nations during the next two years, as
the Fifth committee (Administrative and Budgetary Committee) began
its discussion of the subject.
</P>
<P>
The 2.583 billion dollars proposed budget for 1998 and 1999,
the Secretary-General's first since assuming office this year, is
20.3 million dollars less than that of the current two-year
period. The amount reflects a resource reduction of 124 million
dollars, as well as a 104 million dollars adjustment for inflation
and exchange rates prevailing in December 1996. For the next two
years, the UN chief initially proposed a staffing level of 8,839,
a reduction of 1,182 posts, including the abolition of 904 posts.
(Annan-Budget Proposal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia, Belarus, Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan decided
here Wednesday at a meeting of the parliamentary committee of the
four countries to set up a free-trade zone.
</P>
<P>
Among the 12 resolutions passed at the meeting was the one
providing that value-added tax (VAT) should be levied at the place
of destination of goods rather than the place of production.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, said an Itar-Tass news agency report, also elected
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev chairman of the so-called
"Union of Four" to replace Belarus President Alexander
Lukashenko. (Russia-CIS-Free Trade Zone) 
</P>
</TEXT>
