<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Conference on Medicine Integration to Be Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (Xinhua) -- A world conference to review
and exchange achievements in integrating traditional Chinese
herbal medicines and Western ones will be held in Beijing next week.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,100 scholars and health officials from 22 countries
and regions, as well as the World Health Organization, are expected
to attend the three-day event, reported today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The first World Integrated Medicine Congress, due to open on
Monday, aims to boost the integration of traditional Chinese
herbal medicines and Western ones worldwide and promote
international collaborations in the field, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Chinese Association of the Integration of
Traditional and Western Medicines, the congress will focus on
combining the two approaches for treating such life-threatening
ailments as brain and heart diseases, malignant tumors and
diabetes.
</P>
<P>
Meetings involving satellite transmissions will be organized to
discuss the effects of traditional Chinese herbal medicines on
burns and drug addiction.
</P>
<P>
A special discussion titled "Traditional Chinese Medicine Going
to the World" will be held on Tuesday. Officials and scholars
from the Food and Drug Administration in the United States will
talk about using traditional Chinese herbal medicines in Western
countries by then.
</P>
<P>
Chinese pharmaceutical researchers and officials from the drug
policy and administration bureau of the Ministry of Health, will
lecture on developments of new medicines in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
