wasn't really a question of needing a lot more cash and often
small amounts of training or harsher licensing requirements showed
marked improvements.
</P>
<P>
White House press secretary Mike McCurry said Clinton was "very
keen on stimulating a national discussion," and that the first
couple hoped the meeting "will call national attention to an issue
policymakers historically have ignored."
</P>
<P>
About 75 percent of American families with young children use
some form of child care and most are not pleased with it,
according to a Parents Magazine poll released today.
</P>
<P>
The random poll of some 2,000 parents generated 450 responses
that were projected nationally. 
