<HEADLINE> China Calls on to Respect Varieties of Cultures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 22 (Xinhua) -- As the world was
developing towards globalization and integration, the varieties of
cultures should be respected, Chinese delegate Cui Ying said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the fifty-second session of the General Assembly,
Cui said culture had been playing a more and more important role
in the international relations and the international society had
attached greater importance to the relationship between culture
and development.
</P>
<P>
Cui said the world was so colorful because all countries and
nationalities had their own cultures. Exchanges of cultures
between different countries had reached an unprecedented level in
depth and width.
</P>
<P>
Cui said culture and development were interdependent. Culture
reflected a country's fundamental characteristics of economy and
politics and it helped to promote the development of economy and
politics.
</P>
<P>
Cui said UNESCO would hold its 29th session soon. China hoped
that the session would recommend measures for the further
development of culture in the future. 
</P>
