<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- An economist at the Asian Development Bank said Wednesday
that Southeast Asian economies will experience slower growth and
higher inflation rates this year due to the currency turbulence
afflicting the region.
</P>
<P>
Business World
</P>
<P>
-- Amid regional volatility, the peso Wednesday lost 1.27
percent to average at 34.646 against the U.S. dollar from
Tuesday's 34.223 pesos.
</P>
<P>
Malaya
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine stock market plunged Wednesday after foreign
investors sold down blue chips on continuing concerns over the
peso and low corporate profits for the third quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
