<HEADLINE> Hypo-Bank, Vereinsbank Report Improved Nine-Month Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bonn, October 22 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Hypo-Bank and
Vereinsbank, which will merge into the country's second largest
commercial bank, today reported that their combined operating
results reached 2.3 billion marks (1.29 billion U.S. dollars) in
the first nine months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Vereinsbank chairman Albrecht Schmidt, the designated head of
the future merged bank, said that with a combined balance sheet
total of over 787 billion marks, the future bank would be listed
among the Europe's top five.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Munich said that Vereinbank's
operating results came to 1.29 billion marks, an increase of 26.1
percent from the same period of 1996, while Hypo-Bank's rose 24.2
percent to over one billion marks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
